variables.name: fies_fewfoods
variables.labl: During the last 30 days, was there a time when you or others in your household ate only a few kinds of foods because of lack of money or other resources?

variables.name: fies_skipped

variables.name: fies_ateless

variables.name: fies_ranout

variables.name: fies_ranout_hhs
variables.labl: Following a 'Yes' answer to the question 'During the last 30 days, was there a time when you or others in your household ran out of food because of lack of money or other resources?

variables.name: fies_hungry
variables.labl: In the past 30 days, did you or any household member ever go to sleep at night hungry because there was not enough food?

variables.name: fies_hungry_hhs
variables.labl: Following a 'Yes' answer to the question 'During the last 30 days, was there a time when you or others in your household were hungry but did not eat because there was not enough money or other resources for food?'

variables.name: fies_whlday
variables.labl: In the past 30 days, did you or any household member ever go a whole day and night without eating anything at all because there was not enough food?

variables.name: fies_whlday_hhs
variables.labl: Following a 'Yes' answer to the question 'During the last 30 days, was there a time when you or others in your household went without eating for a whole day because of lack of money or other resources?

variables.name: p_mod
variables.labl: The variable is the probability that the respondent has been exposed to moderate or severe recent food insecurity (experienced in the 4 weeks preceding the survey)

variables.name: p_sev
variables.labl: The variable is the probability that the respondent has been exposed to for severe recent food insecurity (experienced in the 4 weeks preceding the survey).

variables.name: p_ipc3plus
variables.labl: The variable is the probability that the respondent has been exposed to recent food insecurity at severity levels that are equivalent to IPC Phase 3 or more, computed using thresholds set to correspond as closely as possible to the severity levels that id

variables.name: fcs
variables.labl: The Food consumption Score (FCS) is an index that aggregates household-level data on the diversity and frequency of food groups consumed over the last 7 days.

variables.name: fcs_staple_days
variables.labl: How many days over the last 7 days, did members of your household eat starches, roots and tubers such as rice, maize, pasta, bread, sorghum, millet, potato, yam, cassava, white sweet potato?

variables.name: fcs_pulses_days
variables.labl: How many days over the last 7 days, did members of your household eat pulses and nuts such as beans, lentils, cowpeas, soybean, pigeon peas and peanuts or other nuts?

variables.name: fcs_fruit_days
variables.labl: How many days over the last 7 days, did members of your household eat fruits such as local fruits?

variables.name: fcs_meat_fish_days
variables.labl: How many days over the last 7 days, did members of your household eat meat, eggs or fish as a main dish, so not as a condiment?

variables.name: fcs_dairy_days
variables.labl: How many days over the last 7 days, did members of your household consume fresh milk, sour milk, yogurt, cheese or other dairy products [excluding margarine/butter or small amounts of milk for tea/ coffee]?

variables.name: fcs_sugar_days
variables.labl: How many days over the last 7 days, did members of your household consume sugar, or sweet such as sugar, honey, jam, cakes, candy, cookies, pastries, cakes and other sweets and sugary drinks?

variables.name: fcs_oil_days
variables.labl: How many days over the last 7 days, did members of your household eat oil/fat/butter such as vegetable oil, palm oil, groundnut oil, margarine, other fats / oil?

variables.name: fcg
variables.labl: Food Consumption Group.

variables.name: hhs
variables.labl: Household Hunger Scale

variables.name: hhg
variables.labl: Households are divided into five categories based on their household hunger scale (hhs).

variables.name: cs_stress_hh_assets
variables.labl: Over the past 30 days, did anyone in your household have to sell household assets / goods (radio, furniture, television, jewelry, etc.) because of lack of food or money?

variables.name: cs_stress_spent_savings
variables.labl: Over the past 30 days, did anyone in your household have to spend savings because of lack of food or money?

variables.name: cs_stress_sold_more_animals
variables.labl: Over the past 30 days, did anyone in your household have to sell more animals (non-reproductive) than usual because of lack of food or money?

variables.name: cs_stress_borrowed_money
variables.labl: Over the past 30 days, did anyone in your household have to borrow money because of lack of food or money?

variables.name: cs_crisis_sold_prod_assets
variables.labl: Over the past 30 days, did anyone in your household have to sell productive assets or means of transport (sewing machine, wheelbarrow, bicycle, car, etc.) because of lack of food or money?

variables.name: cs_crisis_consumed_seed_stocks
variables.labl: Over the past 30 days, did anyone in your household consume seed stocks that were to be held/saved for the next planting season because of lack of food or money?

variables.name: cs_emergency_hh_migration
variables.labl: Over the past 30 days, did anyone in your household have to migrate with the entire household because of lack of food or money?

variables.name: lcsi
variables.labl: The Livelihood Coping Strategies Index

variables.name: rcsi_less_preferred_foods
variables.labl: In the past 7 days, how many days did your household rely on less preferred or less expensive food due to lack of food/money?

variables.name: rcsi_borrowed_food
variables.labl: In the past 7 days, how many days did your household borrow food, or rely on help from a friend or relative due to lack of food or money to buy food?

variables.name: rcsi_limit_portions
variables.labl: In the past 7 days, how many days did your household limit portion sizes at mealtime due to lack of food or money to buy food?

variables.name: rcsi_restrict_adult_consumption
variables.labl: In the past 7 days, how many days did your household restrict consumption by adults so children could eat, due to lack of food or money to buy food?

variables.name: rcsi_reduce_number_meals
variables.labl: In the past 7 days, how many days did your household reduce the number of meals eaten in a day due to lack of food or money to buy food?

variables.name: rcsi_score
variables.labl: The rCSI is an experience-based indicator measuring the behaviour of households over the past seven days when they did not have enough food or money to purchase food.

variables.name: rcsi_class
variables.labl: Households are divided in four categories according to the rCSI score: 0-3, 4-18, 19-42, and 43 and above. These categories correspond to IPC Phases 1, 2, 3 and 4 and higher respectively.
